## Per-Story Workflow (The Inner Loop)

```
1. SELECT
   - Read prd.json, pick highest-priority story with passes=false and deps satisfied
   - Read progress.txt entries for dependency stories

2. BRANCH
   - git checkout {BRANCH_NAME} (create if needed)
   - git checkout -b story/[ID]

3. UNDERSTAND
   - Read relevant source files
   - Read existing tests if modifying tested code
   - Read any referenced documents

4. EXECUTE
   - Do the work
   - Write tests (if code mode)
   - Keep each logical change as a separate commit if > 1000 LOC total

5. CHECK (mandatory, every commit)
   - Run all build gates
   - If any check fails: read error, fix, re-run (max 3 attempts)
   - If still failing: document, revert, move on

6. REVIEW (self-review before merge)
   Read the full diff: git diff {BRANCH_NAME}..story/[ID]
   Verify:
   - [ ] All acceptance criteria met
   - [ ] No secrets or credentials
   - [ ] No debug/console statements left in
   - [ ] No empty catch blocks
   - [ ] Import paths are clean

7. MERGE
   - git checkout {BRANCH_NAME}
   - git merge story/[ID]
   - git branch -d story/[ID]

8. LOG
   - Update prd.json: set passes: true
   - Append to progress.txt (format below)
   - Commit: {COMMIT_PREFIX}: [ID] - update progress
```

## Progress Format

APPEND to progress.txt:
```
## [Date] - [STORY-ID]
- Topic: [one-liner]
- Changes: [files modified/created/deleted]
- Checks: [verification results]
- Key decisions: [any choices made]
---
```

## Phase Gate Process

At the end of each phase (when all stories in the phase have passes: true):

```
1. FULL VALIDATION
   - Re-run all build gates
   - Verify no regressions from earlier stories

2. PHASE SUMMARY (append to progress.txt)
   ## Phase [N] Complete: [Phase Name]
   - Stories completed: [list]
   - Key changes: [summary]
   ---

3. STOP
   Output: <promise>PHASE_GATE</promise>
   This signals the human to review before proceeding.
```

## Rules

- Be brutally honest in progress.txt about what worked and what didn't.
- If stuck, document the blocker and move on. Don't spin.
- Do NOT create documentation files unless the story specifically calls for it.
- Do NOT format existing code. Only enforce style on new/modified files.

## Stop Condition

If ALL stories in the current phase have `passes: true`:
<promise>PHASE_GATE</promise>

If ALL stories across ALL phases have `passes: true`:
<promise>COMPLETE</promise>

Otherwise, end normally (next iteration picks up the next story).
